sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KServe as KServe Gateway
    participant API as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant Input as InputProcessor<br/>Tokenizer
    participant Engine as EngineCore<br/>Scheduler + KV Cache
    participant Runner as CPU Model Runner<br/>PyTorch CPU
    participant Output as OutputProcessor<br/>Detokenizer
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant OTLP as OTLP Collector<br/>gRPC/HTTP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
    Note over Client,Output: Flow 1: Inference Request Processing
    Client->>KServe: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KServe->>API: Forward request<br/>HTTP(S)/8000
    API->>API: AuthenticationMiddleware<br/>SHA256 hash + constant-time compare
    API->>Input: Parse & validate request<br/>(Pydantic)
    Input->>Input: Tokenize input text<br/>(HF transformers)
    Input->>Engine: Submit tokenized request
    Engine->>Engine: Schedule batch<br/>Manage KV cache pages
    Engine->>Runner: Execute model forward pass
    Runner->>Runner: PyTorch CPU inference<br/>(OpenMP threads)
    Runner-->>Engine: Output token logits
    Engine-->>Output: Scheduled output tokens
    Output-->>API: Detokenized text<br/>(streaming SSE or JSON)
    API-->>KServe: HTTP(S) response
    KServe-->>Client: JSON / SSE stream
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
    Note over API,HF: Flow 2: Model Loading (startup)
    API->>HF: GET model config<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer HF_TOKEN
    HF-->>API: Model configuration
    API->>HF: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer HF_TOKEN
    HF-->>API: Model weight files (safetensors)
    API->>Runner: Load weights into CPU memory<br/>(File I/O → PyTorch tensors)
    Runner->>Runner: Initialize model parameters<br/>in CPU RAM
    end

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
    Note over API,OTLP: Flow 3: Observability
    Prom->>API: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8000
    API-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(request latency, throughput, queue depth)
    API->>OTLP: Export traces<br/>gRPC (insecure) or HTTP
    end
